HEADWORD: madagascar pepper
<hw>madagascar pepper</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
climber (<spn>Piper nigrum</spn>) having dark red berries (peppercorns)
when fully ripe; found in South India and <country>Sri Lanka</country>;
naturalized in North Burma and Assam.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> pepper, common pepper, black pepper, white pepper,
Madagascar pepper, <spn>Piper nigrum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

